<p>Hey,
I&rsquo;ve just been looking for a good plugin that can help me to configure some VIM variables per project.</p>
<p>For example I want <code>set shiftwidth=2</code> for my JavaScript project and <code>set shiftwidth=4</code> for PHP one.</p>
<p>Turned out no plugin needed.</p>
<p>Just put this to your <code>.vimrc</code>:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-vim" data-lang="vim"><span style="display:flex;"><span><span style="color:#a6e22e">silent</span>! <span style="color:#a6e22e">so</span> .<span style="color:#a6e22e">vimlocal</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>Now if you put <code>.vimlocal</code> file to your project root, it will be sourced and &ldquo;executed&rdquo;.</p>
<p><code>silent!</code> is using to supress warnings when there is no .vimlocal file in a directory.</p>